stylometry: You determine total cost of managing a product in inventory by taking the anual total holding cost + the anual total carrying cost. You use a EOQ (economic order quanity) model/equation to figure this out. You want to find the balance between carrying costs and holding costs. Costs incurred from inventory are holding costs, carrying costs, ordering cost,stock cost, and stock outrisk costs. Also, determining when to order is an issue. Having alot of stock means less ordering costs, and having less stock means more ordering costs.
